{South is to play 3NT. West leads the \DK.

Winners:   \S=4  \H=0  \D=1  \C=1  Total = 6

You need 3 more winners, and they must come from the \H suit. The danger is that when you knock out the \HA, West may take too many \Ds. To exhaust East of \Ds you hold-up your \DA until the third round.

Next you start on \Hs by playing \HK, then overtaking the \H10. Assume that East wins the second \H.

You were fortunate it was East who took the \HA, and that he has no \D to return. If he plays a \H or a \S you will win in dummy. If he plays a \C you will jump up with the \CA and take your winners, 9 in all.

You were lucky the \HA was with East.

But if you had not held-up your \DA even good luck wouldn't have helped you.}
[Play "W"]DK

